main event: A witness saw a round or elliptical object approximately 8-9 feet in diameter at an altitude of 1,000 feet, drifting to the southwest in San Diego, California on June 9, 1955.
interesting points: The object was observed for 5,543.3 seconds, which is approximately 92 minutes.
The object was moving at an altitude of about 80,000 feet.
The report concludes that the sighting was probably a balloon.
The report notes that the description of the sighting has the characteristics of a balloon.
No photographs were taken of the object.
sighted object: a round or elliptical object approximately 8-9 feet in diameter
